OL,3,CFrench lifeguard and council guilty
OL,4,Cover girl's death on school trip
OL,6,F"They were afraid that they would not
OL,7,Fget Jessica justice. They were afraid
OL,8,Fthey would be left with their own
OL,9,Fgrief and their struggle alone. But
OL,10,Fnow they have accomplished it, they
OL,11,Fhave seen it through."
OL,13,FDuring the initial trial, the court
OL,14,Fheard how Jessica was hit on the head
OL,15,Fwhen the pontoon flipped over.
OL,17,FShe was rescued by the lifeguard and
OL,18,Fthen airlifted to hospital, but medics
OL,19,Fwere unable to save her.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/8
